cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with action recognition using skeleton-based data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a model using predictive coding, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also mentions using mutual information to maximize the similarity between normal and noisy skeletons, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper uses datasets commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
